Hi,

in this paper:

_Mouret, J.-B. <http://www.isir.upmc.fr/?op=view_profil&lang=fr&id=72> 
and Doncieux, S. <http://www.isir.upmc.fr/?op=view_profil&lang=fr&id=2>_ 
(2012). /Encouraging Behavioral Diversity in Evolutionary Robotics: an 
Empirical Study./
Evolutionary Computation. Vol 20 No 1 Pages 91-133. 
http://www.isir.upmc.fr/files/2011ACLI2061.pdf

we have defined a simplified version of NEAT without innovation numbers. 
We have then used a classical NSGA-II.

Hope it helps,

Stéphane
